cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and semantic networks. The paper also uses tools from the field of network analysis, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The investigation of structural properties of ConceptNet 4 and the analysis of communities suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the investigation of rules suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
